/* =========================================================================
   MoviezDB — i18n.js  (UI translation layer)
   -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Loaded BEFORE shared.js on every page. Exposes:
     App.t(key, vars)      → translated string for the current language
     App.I18n.lang()       → current 2-letter language code (from localStorage)
     App.I18n.dir()        → 'rtl' for Arabic, else 'ltr'
     App.I18n.apply(root)  → translate [data-i18n*] elements + set <html lang/dir>
     App.I18n.applyDocLang()→ just set <html lang/dir> (called immediately)

   The language is whatever App.Lang stored under 'tmdb_lang' (the switcher in
   the nav). Switching reloads the page, so every load simply re-applies the
   right dictionary — no live DOM swapping needed.

   data-i18n        → sets textContent
   data-i18n-html   → sets innerHTML (for titles that contain <span>/<em>)
   data-i18n-ph     → sets placeholder
   data-i18n-title  → sets title attribute
   data-i18n-aria   → sets aria-label

   Movie/show DATA (titles, overviews) is localized by TMDB via the API's
   language param — this file only covers the interface chrome.
   ========================================================================= */
